node.text:
The desire for connection is universal. How we make meaning from moments together and time apart echoes the sentiment strongly: Community matters.​
​
To honour this notion three local Vancouver artists—@tierneymilne, @hannaleejoshi, and @priscillayuart—came together to create a vivid mural in the city where lululemon began.​
​
The artwork depicts a celebration of the bonds we share in all their unique facets and styles. Through shifting perspectives, an openness to collaboration, and embracing non-linear movement, beauty is born.​
​
The artwork is now live in front of our Robson Street store in Vancouver, Canada.

node.text: This bra holds nothing back. (And everything in). Injected foam cups lift and support from underneath, delivering light-as-air comfort and high-support for running and workouts. Tap to shop the new AirSupport Bra.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by lululemon on July 22, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and road.

node.text: Bra breakthroughs don’t happen overnight. We banked five years of research, two years of design, and 576 miles of wear testing to perfect the light-as-air comfort and high support of the new AirSupport Bra. Tap to shop.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by lululemon on July 21, 2021. May be a closeup of 1 person.

node.text: Lift from the cup? Genius. The AirSupport Bra’s injected foam lifts from underneath to re-balance support across the cups, band, and straps. The result: lightweight lift and superior support. The feeling: limitless.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by lululemon on July 20, 2021 tagging @yaavano. May be an image of 1 person, standing and outdoors.

node.text: You don’t give up when the reps get hard, and this gear doesn’t either. Meet the new Power Thru collection—made with snag-resistant, quick-drying fabric that keeps up with your workout. Tap to shop.

The way you move matters. When you approach what you do with intention, things start shifting. This is the guiding philosophy of Aire Libre Running’s “MindWork”.
MindWork explores the concept of movement as an entry point for mindfulness—a deep dive into how our minds and our bodies are connected. When you begin to view exercise and meditation as intertwined, the physical form of movement is simply a medium for exploring the mind.
Discover the connection between movement and meditation during an IG Live conversation with Ambassadors Mau Díaz, Charlie Dark, and Sanchia Legister, moderated by @airelibre.run’s Alex Dickinson.
Learn how they lead with intention Tuesday, July 27 at 12:00 PM PDT.
